  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add chopped onion and minced garlic, saut\u00e9 until translucent.",
    "Fold in bell peppers and stir-fry for about 3 minutes or until slightly soft.",
    "Stir in chicken livers, tomato paste, lemon juice, salt, pepper, and thyme. Cook for another 5-7 minutes.",
    "Pour the entire mixture into a large casserole dish (or any deep pot).",
    "Cover and simmer on low heat for about 1 hour or until the liver is tender.",
    "Serve hot with crusty bread."
